<table width="100%">
<tr><td class="header">Lady Daegarmo at Sony speaks regarding PvP!</td>
<td class="headerblue" align="right">02-03-2002 03:33</td></tr>
</table>
</td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#424954">
Lady Daegarmo who is responsible for all of the BOTB Tournaments involving PvP as well as having considerable PvP development input for Everquest responded to posts such as mine (listed below) and many others.<br />
<br />
In the thread linked below, most everyone admitted there was an extreme inbalance in the way the Teams were created and then evolved with the exception of Ranadiel (the leader of Malignant who is prolly one of those guys who should keep quiet and be THOUGHT a fool than to open his maw and be KNOWN a fool) who stated that the reason the evil team is better is because the more skilled players of Everquest chose the Evil team.<br />
<br />
Although I do not know if her reply was to him (who was about the only person who claimed the teams were balanced), but she did make a CLEAR indication that she is AWARE the teams are inbalanced AND that Manaburn/Lifeburn are out of place in PvP.   Here is the quote:<br />
<br />
<font size="2">I am going to lock this thread as well, and do what has been requested. 4 nights next week I will be holding PvP discussion meetings for each of the PvP servers in EverQuest chat. I will be announcing the times and dates of those chats hopefully later today or Monday morning.<br />
I am not commenting because I am listening, I want to hear what others think, so does the development team.<br />
<br />
Normally I will not debate on issues, but I will state this. <br />
<br />
There is about as much chance of talking me into believing that the darks are an evenly balanced team in means of raw numbers and starting locations as me believing manaburn is perfectly tuned for PvP combat. =)<br />
<br />
Those that wish to smite me for those words, I will see you at the discussions. =)<br />
<br />
Lady Daegarmo</font><br />
<br />
It is my belief that she drips sarcasm in this statement and surely is aware of our problems.  Now to get it fixed!</td></tr>
